<li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Depreciation refers to the amount of capital
that is used up or wears out during each period. For instance,
a machine may have a life expectancy of five years. In order to
measure increases in the capital stock accurately, increases in
investment should be adjusted to reflect depreciation.
