<P><center>
<H2>Gesundheit?</H2><br>
</CENTER>
<P>
<blockquote>

	"Have allergies? Then you might want to move to Albuquerque. That city wants to stop the production of nasty pollen, so it as banned cypress, mulberry, elm, and male juniper trees. The prohibition becomes law later this year. A person can then get slapped with a $500 fine for planting, growing, importing, or selling such trees. Actually, experts say than the ban will have little effect on allergies, as people will get sensitized to other types of pollen."
<P>
         Charles Oliver, <I>Reason</I>, March 1997



</blockquote>
