<H2>Flagging Diversity</H2><br>
</CENTER>
<P>
<blockquote>


	"The theme of Bill Clinton's second inaugural is 'An American Journey,' and this journey over the bridge to the 21st century is represented by a logo showing am American flag made from 'artistically' torn red, white, and blue paper. The blue field is decorated with three human figuresone white, one black, and one brown. (Perhaps for space considerations, perhaps because of Asian-money scandals, no yellow figure is represented.)"
<P>
David Wagner, <I>Insight</I>, February 3, 1997


</blockquote>
