<P><center>
<H2>No Voice if Not Pro-Choice</H2>
</CENTER>
<P>
<blockquote>



	

"The Rev. Patrick J. Mahoney filed suit against Interior Secretary Bruce Babbitt after being denied a permit by the National Park Service to carry pro-life signs on a Pennsylvania Avenue sidewalk during President Clinton's inaugural parade. In a letter from Interior, Mr. Mahoney and members of the Christian Defense Coalition were warned they might be arrested if they showed up for Mr. Clinton's parade with pro-life signs. 'The Clinton administration has betrayed the principles of the First Amendment by threatening to arrest peaceful demonstrators for simply holding signs on a public sidewalk,' Mr. Mahoney says."<P>

John McCaslin, <I>Washington Times</I>, January 14, 1997

</blockquote>
