<P>
<!-------------------------------------------------------------->
<I>for December 3, 1996</I></CENTER>
<P>
<b>Oops</b><br>
Jonathan Yardley, one of the <I>Washington Post</I>'s most sensible regular reviewers and columnists, wrote in Sunday's Book World that "even the most devout Christians" know that Christ wasn't born on Christmas day. Even? Surely Yardley means "especially."
<P>
<b>Truth in Labeling</b><br>
The <I>Washington Post</I> today referred to the possibility that "conservative" Dan Coats might challenge "moderate" Jim Jeffords for the leadership of the Senate Human Relations Committee. For the sake of accuracy, make that "moderately conservative" for Coats and "liberal extremist" for Jeffords.

