<html>

<title>Daily Commentary - January 24, 1997</title>

<body>

<center><h1>Daily Commentary<br>
January 24, 1997</h1></center>

<p><hr width=75% size=3><p>

I'm Gary Bauer for Washington Watch.

<p>

Hold on to your wallets folks, the UN is after your money.  That's
right, the same bunch that brought us the Convention on the Rights
of the Child and the Beijing conference on women is now hitting
us up for over $1 billion.

<p>

And listen to this, they say we <I>owe</I> it to them.  But for
years the United States has been paying a quarter of the UN's
budget, with current contributions costing American taxpayers
$4 billion a year.  And what do we get in return?  Conferences
that push the radical liberal agenda on a global scale, treaties
that sell out American sovereignty and &quot;peacekeeping&quot;
missions that put our soldiers in danger and under foreign command.

<p>

Meanwhile, the UN's bloated bureaucracy continues to grow unchecked.
And the corruption and lavish spending, which are the real reasons
for it's cash shortfall, are ignored.  The nerve of these people;
instead of handing over more money to the UN, the United States
should insist that it get serious about reform by demanding that
they cut staff and stop meddling in the internal affairs of sovereign
nations.  Congress should send back the UN's invoice marked &quot;request
denied.&quot;

<p>

For Family Research Council, this is Gary Bauer with today's
Washington Watch.  For more information about us, call 1-800-225-4008.
That number again:  1-800-225-4008.

<p>

