<title>Daily Commentary - February 4, 1997</title>

<body>

<center><h1>Daily Commentary<br>
February 4, 1997</h1></center>

<p><hr width=75% size=3><p>

I'm Gary Bauer for Washington Watch.

<p>

You know, one of the most depressing things in the fight to defend
human life is watching just how low radical feminists are willing
to go in justifying abortion.

<p>

A new book by Northeastern University political science professor
Eileen McDonagh advocates self-defense as the strongest legal
case for abortion.  That's right, this woman actually says that
unborn children intrude on women's bodies and take their liberty.
She says that if a woman doesn't want this imposition she should
be able to use deadly force to stop it like she would if it were
&quot;rape, kidnapping or slavery.&quot;

<p>

It's difficult to imagine a person so hardened that they'd consider
a defenseless baby a violent intruder.  But it shows just how
out of touch radical feminism is with most women.  Instead of
using terms like &quot;intruder&quot; or &quot;assailant,&quot;
most women think of the life growing in the womb as a baby. 
They think of birth as a blessed event.  God help the pro-abortion
radicals that can't tell the difference between a rapist and a
baby.

<p>

For Family Research Council, this is Gary Bauer with today's
Washington Watch.  For more information about us, call 1-800-225-4008.
That number again:  1-800-225-4008.

<p>

