<TITLE>Gary L. Bauer Publications</TITLE>
<BODY>
<CENTER><H1>Gary L. Bauer Publications</H1>
</CENTER><HR SIZE=3 WIDTH=50%>
<P>
<img src="/townhall/FRC/images/ohod.gif" align=left hspace=12 vspace=12>
<A NAME = "hope"><I>Our Hopes, Our Dreams</I></a><BR>
Gary Bauer<BR>
Focus on the Family Publishing, (Softback, 166pp.) <BR>
Suggested Donation: $3.99
<P>
What do pro-family Americans really want? What would our platform mean to the tax code, to the schools, to the entertainment industry, to business -- and, above all, to our neighborhoods? <i>Our Hopes, Our Dreams</I>, the new book by Gary L. Bauer, Former Undersecretary of Education and White House domestic policy chief, provides an answer to these and other tough questions.<p>
<i>Our Hopes, Our Dreams</i> gives you a concise, affordable resource that explains the pro-family message.<p>

<center><b>
Purchase this book from the 
<a href="http://www.townhall.com/townhall/townhall_shop/welcome.html.cgi">Town 
Hall store</a>
</b></center>

<P><HR><P>

<img src="/townhall/FRC/risk.gif" width=216 height=318 align=left hspace=12 vspace=12>
<A NAME = "children"><I> Children at Risk:  The Battle for the Hearts and Minds of Our Kids</I></a><BR>
Dr. James Dobson and Gary L. Bauer<BR>
Word Publishing, First Edition 1990 (Hardback, 291pp.)<BR>
Suggested Donation: $13.00
<P>
America's foremost family advocate, Dr. James Dobson, and former White House domestic policy adviser Gary Bauer team up in this analysis of the "civil war over values" in contemporary culture.  With candor matched by conviction, Dobson and Bauer describe the challenges parents face raising children in today's moral wilderness.  Each author brings to the book his special expertise:  Dobson as psychologist and author, Bauer as public policy expert and longtime observer of the Washington political scene.  They discuss the sexual revolution, declining respect for human life, the campaign to redefine the family, Washington's failure to defend hearth and home, and much more.

<P>
<BR><BR>

<center><b>
Purchase this book from the 
<a href="http://www.townhall.com/townhall/townhall_shop/welcome.html.cgi">Town 
Hall store</a>
</b></center>

<P><HR><P>

<img src="/townhall/FRC/jour.gif" width=175 height=266 align=left hspace=12 vspace=12>
<A NAME = "journey"><I> Our Journey Home:  What Parents Are Doing to Preserve Family Values</I></a><BR>
Gary Bauer<BR>
Word Publishing, First Edition 1992 (Hardback, 222pp.)<BR>
Suggested Donation: $16.00
<P>
The perfect companion book to<I> Children at Risk</I>, this book describes the emerging signs of a pro-family revival, from trends in public opinion to the new attention being paid to the family in public policy.  Bauer not only describes these developments in detail, but he also offers parents concrete suggestions on how to maintain and strengthen the momentum for family values. <I> Our Journey Home </I>contends that the nation's return to the family comes not a moment too soon, as the corrosive effects of the culture of greed and sexual exploitation threaten the nation's survival.

<P><BR><BR>

<center><b>
Purchase this book from the 
<a href="http://www.townhall.com/townhall/townhall_shop/welcome.html.cgi">Town 
Hall store</a>
</b></center>

