<title>February 4, 1996 Press Release</title>

<body>

<font size=-1>
FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE<br>
February 4, 1996<br>
CONTACT: Kristi S. Hamrick -- (202) 393-2100. For Radio: Kristin Hansen.<br>
FOR AUDIO SOUNDBITES: Call the FRC Direct NewsLine (202)-393-NEWS
</font>

<p>

<center><h2>WHAT'S THE FAMILY TO THINK ABOUT<br>
THE POLICY IN THE STATE OF THE UNION<br>
ADDRESS? ASK GARY BAUER</h2></center>

<p>

<b>WASHINGTON, D.C. --</b> Many of the policy trial balloons
floated in advance of the President's State of the Union address
later today could have been launched from the Family Research
Council.

<p>

Media reports indicate that the President is going to address
a series of pro-family agenda items with long history and significant
study behind them. For information and interviews on many of the
family agenda items addressed, Family Research Council President
Gary L. Bauer along with a number of  well-researched policy analysts
are available.

<p>

Pro-family items said to be in the running for State of  the Union
discussion include:

<p><ul>

<li>$500-per-child tax credit
<li>Tax deductions for school and new big government programs targeting
reading
<li>Estate taxes
<li>Balanced Budget ideas and Social Security
<li>Welfare Reform and church involvement in problem solving
<li>Pell Grants 
<li>Crime and drug problems with America's youth
<li>Human Rights issues and China
<li>Foreign Aid going to international abortion providers <BR>

</ul><p>

FRC's media department will be monitoring (202)-393-2100 ext.
3017 for late breaking questions following the address. FRC analysts
and experts will be available for follow up.

<p>

<center><b>
[<a href="/townhall/FRC/press/press.html">Other Press Releases</a>]
[<a href="/townhall/FRC/subscribe/subscribe.html.cgi">Subscribe to 
our Press Release E-Mail List</a>]
</b></center>

<p>

<HR SIZE = 3>

