<title>January 22, 1996 Press Release</title>

<body>

<font size=-1>
FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE<br>
January 22, 1996 ** 24th Anniversary of <i>Roe v. Wade</i><br>
CONTACT: Kristi S. Hamrick -- (202) 393-2100. For Radio: Kristin Hansen.
</font>

<p>

<center><h2>ABORTION: OUR FINEST MOMENT AS WOMEN?<br>
NO, WOMEN WORTH MORE THAN THAT, SAYS FRC</h2></center>

<p>

<b>WASHINGTON, D.C. --</b> &quot;Liberal feminism has elevated
abortion to something that represents our greatest freedom --
our finest hour as women. But the worth of women is not measured
in the number of abortions, but in our accomplishments as whole
people -- mothers, employers, volunteers, professionals and a
host of other roles,&quot; said Family Research Council Director
of Communication Kristi S. Hamrick on Wednesday -- the 24th anniversary
of <i>Roe v. Wade</i>.

<p>

Mrs. Hamrick made the following statement: &quot;It's odd that
man-hating feminism measures the worth of women by how much they
<I>ACT</I> like men -- whether they have an uninterrupted career
path or push their children into the hobby category. But on this
day, when pro-life Americans reflect on our society, it's clear
that women were misled by this form of feminism. We are not diminished
by childbirth. We become more than who we were.

<p>

&quot;Liberal feminism teaches that children are a parasite or
a millstone to our careers and lives. These so-called women's
advocates say that women are not capable of handling the births
of their children and the capabilities of their minds at the same
time. We must 'choose' one. But when individual 'choice' is elevated
to the constitution, it's not just our children who are injured.
We  see in the euthanasia cases before the Supreme Court that
all the weak become vulnerable when others are given the right
to 'choose' to end their lives.&quot;

<p>

Mrs. Hamrick continued: &quot;Family Research Council condemns
the cowardly acts of people who plant bombs and attack strangers.
The heart of the pro-life message is that the innocent must be
protected. These bombings are unacceptable and must be prosecuted
to the full extent of the law. The pro-life movement seeks to
work within the law to accomplish real change, one life at a time.

<p>

&quot;Family Research Council salutes the pro-life men and women
who work in crisis pregnancy centers, take unwed mothers into
their homes, give of their time and money to families in need
and adopt very wanted children. These Americans are the heart
of the pro-life community and represent America's best response
to women who need help in a difficult time.&quot;

<p>

<center><h3>EDITOR'S NOTE: B-ROLL/PICTURE OPPORTUNITY</h3></center>

<p>

Family Research Council will welcome March for Life participants
for an open house today from 2:30 p.m. to 4 p.m. at the new office
location of 801 G Street N.W.

<p>

