<title>January 16, 1996 Press Release</title>

<body>

<font size=-1>
FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE<br>
January 16, 1996<br>
CONTACT: Kristi S. Hamrick -- (202) 393-2100. For Radio: Kristin Hansen.
</font>

<p>

<center><h2>'VIOLENCE IS NOT AN ANSWER TO VIOLENCE'</h2>
<h4>Gary L. Bauer Statement following<br>
1/16/97 Atlanta Abortion Clinic Bombing:</h4></center>

<p>

<b>WASHINGTON, D.C. --</b> Family Research Council President Gary
L. Bauer made the following statement Thursday following media
reports of an abortion clinic bombing in Atlanta:

<p>

&quot;Violence is not an answer to violence. That is especially
clear on the eve of the nation's observance of Martin Luther King
Day.

<p>

&quot;Dr. King galvanized a movement to correct a profound injustice,
but he used peaceful means to accomplish the highest goals. Millions
of Americans are frustrated by the deaths of millions of children
through abortion. But we have sought and must continue to seek
loving solutions, honest public debate and sound legislation.

<p>

&quot;We are very thankful to learn through the news media that
no employee of the clinic was killed in this dreadful incident.
Family Research Council condemns today's acts of violence in Atlanta.&quot;

<p>

