<center><h2>ATTENTION EDITORS AND REPORTERS:

<p>

<i>&quot;ON DRUGS<br>
THE CLINTON ADMINISTRATION'S CURIOUS<br>
SURRENDER&quot;</i></h2>

<p>

<h4>Available NOW along with other policy works
on the growing drug problem in America.</h4></center>

<p>

<b>WASHINGTON, D.C. --</b> &quot;The policy debate over the drug
problem has radically changed from one that tried to find effective
ways of keeping our children from drugs to 'harm reduction' strategies
which facilitate 'safer' drug use ... and you can see the result
of that seriously flawed switch,&quot; said Robert L. Maginnis,
drug policy analyst for the Family Research Council. The policy
expert made his comments as more evidence was unveiled this week
on the growing drug crisis in America.

<p>

&quot;Illicit drugs kill 20,000 Americans every year,&quot; Maginnis
noted. &quot;We must get serious about the life and death struggle
that casual attitudes toward drug use ignore.&quot;

<p>

Other policy papers available from the Family Research Council
looking at drug use:

<p><ul>

<li>&quot;<a href="/townhall/FRC/perspective/pv96b3dr.html">New Commander for 
Three-Front Drug War</a>&quot; on General Barry McCaffrey
<li>&quot;<a href="/townhall/FRC/insight/is96d4dr.html">Mary Jane is No 
Florence Nightingale: The Truth About Marijuana's Medicinal Uses</a>&quot;
<li>&quot;<a href="/townhall/FRC/perspective/pv96c2dr.html">Revamping 
the Drug War</a>&quot;
<li>&quot;<a href="/townhall/FRC/infocus/if95j1dr.html">Adolescent 
Marijuana Abuse Goes Higher</a>&quot;
<li>&quot;<a href="/townhall/FRC/insight/is95g1dr.html">Drug Abuse 
Prevention: How to Keep Kids Drug Free</a>&quot;
<li>&quot;<a href="/townhall/FRC/infocus/if95g1dr.html">Survey Links 
Illegal Drug Use to Popular Culture</a>&quot;
<li>&quot;<a href="/townhall/FRC/insight/is96g1dr.html">Federal Drug 
War Ignoring Great Ally: Faith-Based Treatment</a>&quot;
<li>&quot;<a href="/townhall/FRC/insight/is96c3dr.html">Designer Drugs 
Make A Comeback</a>&quot;
<li>&quot;<a href="/townhall/FRC/insight/is95c2dr.html">Legalization of 
Drugs: The Myths and the Facts</a>&quot;
<li>&quot;<a href="/townhall/FRC/insight/is95b3dr.html">Back to the 
'70s: The MTV Generation Inhales</a>&quot;
<li>&quot;<a href="/townhall/FRC/insight/is96e1dr.html">Will Exchanging 
Needles Save America's Future?</a>&quot;
<li>&quot;National Drug Abuse Policy Plank&quot;
<li>&quot;Why the Intelligent Poll Should Support a Tough Line on
Drugs&quot;
<li>Along with op-ed pieces such as: &quot;Don't Relax War on Drugs&quot;

</ul><p>

