<center><h2>IN THE NEWS:<br>
PRO-LIFE VICTORIES ACROSS THE COUNTRY<br>
AND IN SAN DIEGO</h2>

<p>

<h4>GARY L. BAUER RECOGNIZED AS AUTHORITATIVE
SPOKESMAN  FOR PRO-LIFE AMERICA TODAY IN <i>NEW YORK TIMES,
WASHINGTON POST</i>, AND OTHER MAJOR MEDIA</h4></center>

<br><p>

<h4>REASONS WHY LIFE ISSUE A MUST FOR POLITICAL COVERAGE THIS 
WEEK:</h4>

<p>
<li>Pro-life candidates win all three primaries -- Georgia, Kansas
and Michigan.

<p>

<li>These included:

<p><ul>

-- the fight for Dole's senate seat<br>
-- the Speaker's home state<br>
-- the state of a governor who has been on the short list of
Vice Presidential candidates

</ul><p>

<li><I>New York Times'</I> polling shows what Gary Bauer has said
all along, the people making up the GOP delegation are primarily
pro-life.

<p>

<li>To the contrary of what pro-abortion Republicans have said,
the platform remains a document that reflects the majority view
of the GOP -- that life is an important issue.

<p>

<li>Gary Bauer continues to be a champion in the fight for life,
meeting with the majority of the delegation repeatedly during
these days to find reasonable ground.

