<LI> Garry Wills contributes an apologia pro Bill Clinton to the  <I>New York Times Magazine</I>, which ends by assuring us that the President's sexual curriculum vitae is no worse than that of Republican divorcees like Dole, Gingrich, Gramm, Armey, et. al. But none of these men stands accused of arranging an assignation by sending the cops to fetch an employee to a hotel roomevidently a distinction which Mr. Wills, the former seminarian, considers Jesuitical.
<P>
<LI> Leonoso Canales of Kingsville, Texas, is not easily fooled: "I see hell in hello. It's disguised by the o, but once you see it, it will slap you in the face." His solution: use "heaven-o" instead. The commissioners of Kleberg County unanimously designated "heaven-o" as the county's official greeting, and just wait till they start thinking about raisins.
</blockquote>


