<!-------------------------------------------------------------->
<center><b>January 16, 1997</b></center>
<HR WIDTH=50%>
<P>
<P>
<blockquote>


	




 <LI>A wildlife park in South Africa is having problems: young male elephants are raping and killing and rhinoceroses, attacking and killing tourists. The Rhino and Elephant Foundation of Johannesburg says the juvenile delinquents are orphans who grew up without the early supervision of their mothers and other adult females, and when they reached the age of 15, a time of increased sex drive and aggression, they lacked the stern supervision of the older males to keep them on the right path. Sound familiar? 
<P>
<LI> David Brudnoy, author of the best-selling <I>Life Is Not A Rehearsal</I>, popular Boston talk-radio host, and an <I>NR</I> contributor, will be a guest on <I>NR Online</I> editor Chris Weinkopf's Internet talk-radio program Thursday. You can catch the live broadcast at <a href="http://www.grit.com">www.grit.com</a> from 1:15 to 1:45 p.m. EST, or listen on-demand any time after 10 a.m. Friday. If you have any questions for Mr. Brudnoy, send them to 
<a href="mailto:chris@grit.com">chris@grit.com</a>.


</blockquote>


