<TITLE>DANIEL J. MITCHELL -- Heritage </TITLE>

<H3>DANIEL J. MITCHELL</H3>
<HR>
<B>MCKENNA SENIOR FELLOW IN POLITICAL ECONOMY</B>
<P><IMG SRC="/heritage/staff/pics/mitchell.gif" ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=10>
<P>
Mitchell previously served as an economist examining budgetary and tax matters for Sen. Bob Packwood, R-Ore., then-ranking minority member of the Senate Finance Committee. A former Director of Tax and Budget Policy at Citizens for a Sound Economy, Mitchell served in 1989 on President Bush's Independent Agencies Transition Team, analyzing the Federal Reserve System. Mitchell is a co-host for Mitchells in the Morning on National Empowerment Television, a conservative cable  network.  A Ph.D. candidate in economics at George Mason University, Mitchell has an M.A. from the University of Georgia.

