<html><head><title>SBSC Issues:  The Citizen Congress Act</title></head><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<center><h2>The Citizen Congress Act</h2><hr width="45%" size="4"><P>
</center>
Representatives Mark Sanford (R-SC) and Wayne Allard (R-CO) and
Senator Bill Frist (R-TN) recently introduced the Citizen Congress
Act.  This  legislation promises to bring our elected officials
closer to home.  While important reforms such as term limits have
lost steam, the Citizen Congress Act is gaining momentum as an
alternative reform channel.  SBSC encourages you to notify your
U.S. Representatives and Senators of your support for this initiative.
<P>
For more information, access the  SBSC <a href="/sbsc/pr111695.html">press release</a> on the Citizens
Congress Act.

<P>
Send a letter to the following Senators and Congressman expressing your support for the Citizens Congress Act:<p>

<a href="/sbsc/l-cca-sanford.html">Congressman Mark Sanford</a><br>
<a href="/sbsc/l-cca-frist.html">Senator Bill Frist</a><br>
<a href="/sbsc/l-cca-gephardt.html">Minority Leader Richard Gephardt</a><br>
<a href="/sbsc/l-cca-daschle.html">Minority Leader Tom Daschle</a><br>
<a href="/sbsc/l-cca-ford.html">Minority Whip Wendell Ford</a><p>

You can also print out a letter to send to your <a href="/sbsc/l-cca-congress.txt">Congressman</a> or <a href="/sbsc/l-cca-senate.txt">Senator</a>.<p>
<br>

[ <a href="/sbsc/home.html">SBSC Home</a> | <a href="/sbsc/letters.html">Letters to Congress</a> ]
</center></body></html>

