<htmL><HEAD><title>SBSC Issues:  Davis-Bacon Repeal</title></head><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><center><h2>Davis-Bacon Repeal</h2><p><hr size="4" width="45%"></center>
<P>SBSC has fought hard for the repeal of the notorious Davis-Bacon Act.  This Act was enacted six decades ago in an effort to reduce the influx of black southern workers into northern federal construction projects.  The Act grants the federal government power to determine an area's "prevailing wage."  This anti-market provision has resulted in driving the costs of construction up, thereby increasing costs to taxpayers, while simultaneously creating a large paperwork burden.  Davis-Bacon has prevented small construction firms, who cannot afford to pay the inflated prevailing wages, from competing for federal construction projects.  Davis-Bacon has also prevented many contractors from hiring minority and unskilled workers, who are denied employment opportunity due to hiring preferences resulting from Davis-Bacon.
<P>
Davis-Bacon repeal was recently taken out of the Republican budget bill, and some members of Congress wish to strengthen Davis-Bacon (which they mistakingly call "reform") by applying it to off-site construction. The Department of Labor recently imposed Davis-Bacon wage and paperwork requirements on those who build ships for the federal government.  Obviously, it is important that we step up the fight for Davis-Bacon repeal.  
<P><i>See Karen Kerrigan's testimony "<a href="/sbsc/ct2-15-5.html">Repeal of the Davis Bacon Act</a>", or Raymond Keating's "<a href="/sbsc/reg1-5.html">Repeal the Davis Bacon Act</a>" for more information.</i>
<P>
Send a letter to the following Senators and Congressman expressing your opposition to the Davis-Bacon Act:<p>

<a href="/sbsc/l-dbr-gephardt.html">Minority Leader Richard Gephardt</a><br>
<a href="/sbsc/l-dbr-daschle.html">Minority Leader Tom Daschle</a><br>
<a href="/sbsc/l-dbr-ford.html">Minority Whip Wendell Ford</a><p>

You can also print out a letter to send to your <a href="/sbsc/l-dbr-congress.txt">Congressman</a> or <a href="/sbsc/l-dbr-senate.txt">Senator</a>.<p>
<br>

<hr><P><center>
[ <a href="/sbsc/home.html">SBSC Home</a> | <a href="/sbsc/letters.html">Letters to Congress</a> ]</center>
</body></html>
