<P>
<B>SUNY's Core Curricula: The Failure to Set Consistent &amp;
High Academic Standards</B>
<P>
Empire Foundation for Policy Research<HR>

<P>
In an attempt to discover why intellectual standards have fallen
and students' knowledge has declined in basic areas of education,
the New York Association of Scholars and the Empire Foundation
for Policy Research commissioned this study of the campuses of
the State University of New York. They discovered a nationwide
trend in whereby students take an odd mixture of courses that
do not build on previous knowledge, while avoiding more fundamental
and serious subjects. For example, one campus mandates that students
take courses in physical education while at the same time does
not require courses in history, literature, philosophy, arts,
English composition, mathematics or science. In addition, intellectual
permissiveness and political correctness are running rampant on
these campuses with courses such as, &quot;Literature of Sports,&quot;Deviance,&quot;
