<b>The Bionomics Institute: 4th Annual 
Bionomics Conference</b><br>
San Francisco, CA: October 18-19<p>
This year's conference will center on the issue: <I>Cultivating the Netconomy</I>. The keynote speaker will be Margaret Wheately, the author of <I>Management and the New Science</I>.  Other featured speakers include: James Pinkerton, author, <I>What Comes Next</I>; Ed Crane, President, Cato Institute; Robert Axtell and Joshua Epstein, creators of SugarScape; Phil Burgess, President, Center for the New West; Bernardo Huberman, Research Fellow, Xerox PARC; Stan Davis, author, <I>Future Perfect</I>; Deborah Gordon, Assistant Professor, Stanford University; Paul Saffo, President, Institute for the Future; Richard Pryor, Program Director, Sandia National Laboratories; Morley Winograd, author <I>Taking Control: Politics in the Information Age</I>; Peter Denning, Associate Dean, George Mason University; Bob Poole, President, Reason Foundation; Steven Rooke, Digital Artist; and Michael Rothchild, President, The Bionomics Institute.  Contact: The Bionomics Institute, 415/454-1000, Internet <a href="http://www.bionomics.org">http://www.bionomics.org.</a><p>
