<b>State Policy Network's Fourth Annual Meeting</b><br>
Minneapolis, MN: September 20, 21<p>
This year's meeting will be held at the Radisson Plaza Hotel in downtown Minneapolis. CONTACT: State Policy Network, 816 Mill Lake Road, Fort Wayne, IN 46845, 219/637-7778, fax 219/637-7779.
<p><hr><p><b>
Harvard School of Public Health: Analyzing Risk: Science, Assessment, and Management</b><br>
Boston, MA: September 24-27<p>
This conference will provide an opportunity for regulatory, industrial, and public health professionals to acquire or enhance their skills in risk assessment, risk management, and risk communication. Dr. John Graham will lead a series of lectures and discussions to help equip professionals for the challenges they face involving occupational and environmental hazards.  The three day conference will specifically target problems involving chemicals and radiation, focusing on the principles of toxicology and epidemiology, possible uses for risk analysis, and the challenges of risk communication.  CONTACT: Nicola Costa, Center for Continuing Professional Education,, 677 Huntington Avenue, Dept. A, Boston, MA, 02115-6023, 617/432-1171, fax 617/432-1969
