The NRC, a nonprofit organization that promotes cost-effectiveness in social service programs, is undertaking a "results-based evaluation project" for job training and employment programs that may be of interest to public policy research organizations in the United States. The NRC will provide inexpensive, pertinent, and timely information about the relative cost-effectiveness of social service programs on a local, state, and national basis to funders, service providers, the general public, legislators, potential customers, and researchers. <p>CONTACT: National Results Council, 2677 North Innsbruck Drive, Suite E, St. Paul, MN 55112, 612/604-0366, fax 612/604-0367.
