<CENTER><FONT SIZE=5>
EVENTS</font></center>
<p><br>
<b>American Legislative Exchange Council</b>
<br>
Washington, D.C.: May 29 to June 2<br>
The American Legislative Exchange Council will host their annual National Leadership Summit at the Omni Hotel in Cincinnati, Ohio from May 29th to June 2nd. The centerpiece for the five-day meeting will be deregulation of the electric and telecommunications industries, and will bring together major leaders from the state legislative and private sector in order to develop policies that will ensure a smooth transition to a competitive marketplace for these major components in the American economy. 
<p>CONTACT: American Legislative Exchange Council, 910 17th Street, N.W., Fifth Floor, Washington, D.C. 20006, 202/759-3434, fax 202/466-3801.
