<B><font size=3>Briefing Book: The Case Against the Federal Legal Services Program<p><i>National Legal and Policy Center</i>  
</FONT></B>
<P>
This briefing book was compiled to provide opinion leaders with the latest data and analysis on the federal 
legal services program. Through the Legal Services Corporation (LSC), the federal government funds over 
300 private groups for the direct purpose of providing legal representation for the poor in civil matters. 
NLPC believes that LSC has failed in its mission and that the federal legal services program should be 
ended. Also included is a chapter on the illegal LSC survival campaign from a 1985 book entitled Legal 
Services Corporation: The Robber Barons of the Poor, published by the Washington Legal Foundation. 
The book also includes other publications criticizing LSC by the Heritage Foundation, National Review, 
Manhattan Institute, and Capital Research Center. 123 pp. CONTACT: National Legal and Policy Center, 
