<B><font size=3> Revitalizing Our Cities: Perspectives From America's New Breed of Mayors, 
</FONT></B><font size=3 FACE="Times New Roman">edited by
William Eggers</FONT>
<p>
<I><font size=3>Policy Study </FONT></I><font size=3 FACE="Times New Roman">No.
185, Washington Institute for Political Studies</FONT>
<P>
This paper includes series of speeches on city privatization efforts from the mayors of some of Americas 
biggest cities. This collection, edited by William Eggers of the Reason Foundation, is the second of seven 
How-To-Guides the Washington Institute will publish on privatization and contracting out services. 
Elaine Davis, Research Fellow at the Washington Institute, introduces the report, summarizes the mayors 
