<B>The Center for Economic Personalism Summer Research Fellowships</B>
<P>
The Center for Economic Personalism is an academic
research facility in Grand Rapids, Michigan, whose purpose is
to promote dialogue between free-market economic theory and Christian
social thought. The general theme for the Summer 1996 Research
Program is the historical and philosophical foundations of both
Christian social thought and Austrian economics. The goal will
be to trace general historical developments of both traditions
and to search for common ground in methodological principles and
philosophical sources. Applicants should possess an earned Ph.D.
in Philosophy, Theology, Economics or Social Thought, and have
a strong commitment to free-market ideas and Christian social
thought. The Center will pay all travel expenses, housing costs
and award a modest stipend for a two month commitment between
June 15th and August 15th 1996. Applications should include a
C.V. and a statement of interest in the project. CONTACT: Dr.
Gregory Gronbacher, Center for Economic Personalism, The Acton
Institute, 161 Ottawa Avenue, N.W., Suite 301, Grand Rapids, Michigan
49503, 616/454-3080, e-mail <a href="mailto: ggbacher@acton.org">ggbacher@acton.org</a>, Internet <a href="http://www.acton.org">http://www.acton.org</a>.
