<B>Advisory Commission on Intergovernmental Relations
Conference on Federal Mandates</B>
<P>
Washington, DC: March 6-7
<P>
March 1996 marks the first anniversary of the <I>Unfunded
Mandates Reform Act of 1995</I>. However, relief from existing
mandates requires additional legislative  or executive action.
which issues should be addressed? which should be modified or
eliminated? How much real relief can states and localities expect?
How will regulators be affected? On March 6-7, 1996, the Advisory
Commission on Intergovernmental relations will hold a Conference
on federal mandates at the Washington Hilton to address these
questions. Speakers will survey the current state of mandate reform
and recent relief measures, Congressional proposals, key issues
that will shape the course of future debate, and the real effects
of change on states, municipalities, and federal agencies. CONTACT:
Advisory Commission on Intergovernmental Relations, 703/883-9363.
