<B><font size=3>The Fiscal Survey of the States</FONT></B>
<P>
<font size=3>National Governors' Association</FONT>


<P>
<font size=3>The Fiscal Survey of the States is published twice
annually by the National Association of State Budget Officers
and the National Governors' Association, and presents aggregate
and individual data on states' general fund receipts, expenditures
and balances. The report found that about half the states enacted
tax cuts</FONT><I><font size=3 FACE="Times New Roman">-</FONT></I><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Times New Roman">reacting
to moderate economic growth and policy goals to downsize government.
The survey also reports findings in the following areas: state
spending, state revenue actions, year-end balances, regional outlook,
state restructuring, and federal aid. 56 pp. CONTACT: National
Governors' Association, 444 North Capital Street, Suit 267, Washington,
D.C. 20001-1512, (202)624-5382.<BR>
