on Florida's Public Policy Issues</FONT></B>
<P>
<font size=3>The Foundation for Florida's Future</FONT>


<P>
<font size=3>The Foundation for Florida's Future, as its first
major research project, has conducted a comprehensive survey on
the concerns and opinions of African-Americans in Florida. According
to the report, the ultimate intention of the survey was to take
the first step in the process of building bridges between whites
and blacks. The survey had three major findings: 1) to date, conservatives
have failed to communicate their message to the black community;
2) the political labels of &quot;conservative&quot; and &quot;liberal&quot;
are meaningless in the dialogue, because action is what counts;
and 3) language and perception account for most differences, while
position on most issues are similar. 20 pp. CONTACT: Foundation
