<B><font size=3>Friedrich A. Hayek Fellowships</FONT></B>
<P>
<font size=3 FACE="Times New Roman">The Board of Directors of
The Mont Pelerin Society have announced the Friedrich A. Hayek
Fellowships for the 1996 General Meeting of The Mont Pelerin Society
to be held in Vienna, Austria from September 8th through 13th,
1996. The Hayek Fellowships will be awarded for the three best
essays on the topic: &quot;Responsibility and Choice in a Free
Society.&quot; Essays of not more than 5,000 words may be submitted
by students or young faculty members 35 years of age or younger,
who are not members of The Mont Pelerin Society. The essays will
be judged by a panel of three senior members of The Mont Pelerin
Society. Deadline for submission of essays is April 30, 1996.
First prize Hayek Fellow Award of $2,500 + $1,000 travel grant
to participate in the Society's Vienna meeting. Second prize Hayek
Fellow Award of $1,500 + $1,000 travel grant to participate in
the Society's Vienna meeting. Third prize Hayek Fellow Award of
$1,000 + $1,000 travel grant to participate in the Society's Vienna
meeting. Further information is available from: <a href="/heritage/mpsad.html">The Mont Pelerin Society</a>, P.O. Box 7031, Alexandria, Virginia 22307.<BR>
</FONT>
